{"word":"H7122 - קָרָא - qârâʼ - kaw-raw' - Befall","slug":"H7122","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָרָא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qârâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-raw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Befall"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05E8;&#x05D0; - qa&#x0302;ra&#x0302;'</b> - <i>kaw-raw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>encounter</i>, whether accidentally or in a hostile manner: - befall, (by) chance, (cause to) come (upon), fall out, happen, meet."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7125\">H7125</a>"}]}